******
[2]
Date: 18 Jun 2011
Source: The New India Express [edited]
http://ibnlive.in.com/news/seven-more-anthrax-cases-reported/160509-60-117.html


More anthrax cases reported
----------------------------------------
MKCG Medical College and Hospital here received another 7 persons
with symptoms of anthrax on Thursday night [16 Jun 2011]. They belong
to Mahulpada village. Anthrax scare gripped Kandhamal district after 8
persons of Guchuka were shifted to Berhampur for treatment on 11 Jun
2011. Swab and blood tests of 4 affected persons were found positive.
As many as 25 persons of villages in Tumudibandh block have contracted
the disease.

The disease reportedly affected the villagers after they consumed
meat of dead animals. The disease has claimed many animals and a
veterinarian from Cuttack has reached the affected areas to assess the
situation.

The spread of the disease, despite Government's claims that the
situation is under control, has many villagers packing bags for some
safer localities.

--
